IssueType.name: Bug
IssueType.description: A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.

IssueType.name: Auto-Ticket
IssueType.description: This ticket was generated by an external source

IssueType.name: Analysis Request
IssueType.description: A request for data processing work.

IssueType.name: Bug Sub-Task
IssueType.description: For when the sub-task is a bug

IssueType.name: Improvement Sub-Task
IssueType.description: For when the sub-task is an improvement

IssueType.name: Invalid Data Sub-Task
IssueType.description: For when the sub-task is invalid data

IssueType.name: New Feature Sub-Task
IssueType.description: For when the sub-task is a new feature

IssueType.name: Paper
IssueType.description: Issue to track the assignment of writing a paper

IssueType.name: New Feature
IssueType.description: A new feature of the product, which has yet to be developed.

IssueType.name: Task
IssueType.description: A task that needs to be done.

IssueType.name: Improvement
IssueType.description: An improvement or enhancement to an existing feature or task.

IssueType.name: Prokaryotic Annotation
IssueType.description: Issue to track the annotation of an organism

IssueType.name: Invalid Data
IssueType.description: There is a problem with data integrity

Priority.name: Blocker
Priority.description: Blocks development and/or testing work, production could not run.

Priority.name: Critical
Priority.description: Crashes, loss of data, severe memory leak.

Priority.name: Minor
Priority.description: Minor loss of function, or other problem where easy workaround is present.

Priority.name: Trivial
Priority.description: Cosmetic problem like misspelt words or misaligned text.

Resolution.name: Fixed
Resolution.description: A fix for this issue is checked into the tree and tested.

Resolution.name: Won't Fix
Resolution.description: The problem described is an issue which will never be fixed.

Resolution.name: Duplicate
Resolution.description: The problem is a duplicate of an existing issue.

Resolution.name: Incomplete
Resolution.description: The problem is not completely described.

Resolution.name: Cannot Reproduce
Resolution.description: All attempts at reproducing this issue failed, or not enough information was available to reproduce the issue. Reading the code produces no clues as to why this behavior would occur. If more information appears later, please reopen the issue.

Resolution.name: Not A Bug
Resolution.description: The issue reported works as designed.

Resolution.name: Work Complete
Resolution.description: The required action has been completed

Status.name: Open
Status.description: The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.

Status.name: In Progress
Status.description: This issue is being actively worked on at the moment by the assignee.

Status.name: Reopened
Status.description: This issue was once resolved, but the resolution was deemed incorrect. From here issues are either marked assigned or resolved.

Status.name: Resolved
Status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

Status.name: Closed
Status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.

Status.name: Submitted to GenBank
Status.description: Sample Tracking: Sample has been submitted to Genbank and is awaiting approval / confirmation
